<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-26T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-26T16:00:00-05:00" n="75" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d75">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763. 72114/2804</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-26T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 26, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1058. Department’s 928, August [<hi rend="italic">September</hi>] 17, 4
                                p.m.<note n="1" xml:id="d75fn1">Not printed; see Department’s
                                telegram No. 815, Aug. 4, <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>
                            </note> Department still awaiting reply from German Government regarding
                            reciprocal release sanitary personnel. This Government is ready to
                            release members of German sanitary personnel held in this country and to
                            request safe-conducts from British and French Governments as soon as
                            favorable reply is received from German Government.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>